article.headline: DePaul shoots 52 percent in victory
article.linkText: Dant's 29 points help DePaul rout USC
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Jenni Dant scored 29 points to lead No. 20 DePaul
to a 99-77 victory over Southern California on Saturday.

Allie Quigley scored 21 points, and Khara Smith added 18 points
and 11 rebounds for the Blue Demons (2-0).

DePaul shot 52 percent and held USC under 40 percent shooting.
DePaul shot 8-for-18 from 3-point range.

Jamie Hagiya scored 14 points and Rachel Woodward added 13 to
lead the Trojans (1-1). Jamie Funn scored 12 and Meghan Gnekow and
Camille LeNoir each had 10.

DePaul led 45-39 at halftime.
